name: Arulmiku Sri Nagaraja Temple
description: Nagaraja Temple is dedicated to Nagaraja, the serpent god, and is one of the few temples in India where snakes are worshipped. The temple has a unique architecture with its main deity being a five-headed serpent. The temple premises also house shrines for Shiva and Anantha Krishna. Devotees believe that the soil inside the temple has curative properties for skin ailments.
